---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import business from '../data/business.json';
---

<Base
  title="Succession Planning"
  description="The North American Upholstery Guild helps upholstery business owners plan for retirement, transition their business, and preserve the legacy they've built."
>
  <!-- Page Header -->
  <section class="page-header noise-grain">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Business Succession & Transition</h1>
      <hr class="divider divider-center page-divider" />
      <p class="page-subtitle">
        When you're ready to step back, your business doesn't have to close its doors.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Intro -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-narrow">
      <h2>Your Business Is Worth Preserving</h2>
      <hr class="divider" />
      <p>
        You've spent decades building something real; a reputation, a client base,
        a workshop full of hard-won knowledge. The question every experienced
        upholsterer eventually faces is: what happens to all of this when I'm ready
        to retire?
      </p>
      <p>
        Too often the answer is "it just closes." The clients scatter, the equipment
        gets sold at auction, and years of expertise walk out the door. The Guild
        believes there's a better path.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our Business Succession program is designed to help owners transition on
        their own terms, whether that means finding a buyer, mentoring a successor,
        or having the Guild itself step in to continue operations under your
        established name.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How It Works -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>How the Guild Helps</h2>
      <hr class="divider" />

      <div class="steps-grid">
        <div class="step-card">
          <div class="step-number">01</div>
          <h3>Confidential Consultation</h3>
          <p>
            We start with a private conversation about your goals, your timeline,
            and what matters most to you; whether that's maximizing value, ensuring
            staff continuity, or preserving your brand in the community.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="step-card">
          <div class="step-number">02</div>
          <h3>Business Valuation</h3>
          <p>
            Our team helps you understand what your business is actually worth. Your
            equipment, client relationships, contracts, reputation, goodwill.
            No guesswork, no lowballs.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="step-card">
          <div class="step-number">03</div>
          <h3>Transition Planning</h3>
          <p>
            We work with you to structure a transition that fits your situation.
            That could mean a full acquisition, a phased retirement where you
            stay on in an advisory role, or connecting you with a qualified buyer
            from within the Guild network.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="step-card">
          <div class="step-number">04</div>
          <h3>Continuity & Legacy</h3>
          <p>
            When the Guild acquires a business, we keep the name on the door,
            retain existing staff wherever possible, and honor the relationships
            you've built. Your clients continue to receive the quality they expect.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who This Is For -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-narrow">
      <h2>Who This Is For</h2>
      <hr class="divider" />
      <p>
        This program is for upholstery business owners who are thinking about
        the next chapter, whether retirement is five years away or five months away.
        You don't need to have a decision made. You don't need to be a current
        Guild member. You just need to be open to a conversation.
      </p>
      <p>
        We work with shops of all sizes, from one-person operations to multi-employee
        businesses. Every situation is different, and we tailor our approach accordingly.
      </p>

      <div class="who-list">
        <div class="who-item">
          <h4>Approaching Retirement</h4>
          <p>You've been doing this for decades and you're starting to think about what comes next.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="who-item">
          <h4>No Clear Successor</h4>
          <p>Your children aren't interested in the trade, and you don't have an apprentice ready to take over.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="who-item">
          <h4>Ready for a Change</h4>
          <p>You still love the craft but the business side has worn you down. You'd rather do the work without running the shop.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="who-item">
          <h4>Health or Life Changes</h4>
          <p>Circumstances have changed and you need a reliable path to transition sooner than planned.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section cta-section noise-grain">
    <div class="container cta-inner">
      <h2>Start the Conversation</h2>
      <p>
        There's no obligation and everything is confidential. Reach out when you're
        ready. We're here to listen and help you think through your options.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-actions">
        <a href={`tel:${business.telephone}`} class="btn btn-accent">Call {business.telephoneDisplay}</a>
        <a href={`mailto:${business.email}?subject=Succession%20Planning%20Inquiry`} class="btn btn-cta-outline">Email Us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-header {
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 3.5rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .page-header h1 { color: #fff; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .page-divider { background: var(--color-accent); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .page-subtitle { font-size: 1.1rem; opacity: 0.9; max-width: 600px; margin-inline: auto; }

  .content-narrow {
    max-width: 750px;
  }

  .content-narrow p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  /* Steps */
  .steps-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .step-card {
    padding: 1.75rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-top: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
  }

  .step-number {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.5;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .step-card h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .step-card p {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  /* Who List */
  .who-list {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .who-item {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-primary);
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
  }

  .who-item h4 {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
    color: var(--color-primary-dark);
  }

  .who-item p {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* CTA */
  .cta-section {
    background: var(--color-primary-dark);
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .cta-section h2 { color: #fff; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .cta-inner p { font-size: 1.05rem; opacity: 0.9; max-width: 550px; margin: 0 auto 2rem; }

  .cta-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .btn-cta-outline {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.75rem 2rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    border: 2px solid #fff;
    border-radius: 4px;
    color: #fff;
    transition: background 0.2s, color 0.2s;
  }

  .btn-cta-outline:hover {
    background: #fff;
    color: var(--color-primary-dark);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .steps-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
